# Groq (https://console.groq.com/keys)
# - /api/analyze (PHOTOS): the key is REQUIRED — the vision model estimates the
#   visual evidence that the rule engine maps to a body type.
# - /api/analyze-measurements (MEASUREMENTS): the key is OPTIONAL — the body type
#   is computed deterministically in code. The key is only used to personalize the
#   styling copy; without it, curated preset copy is used.
# Vercel: add the same variable in Project → Settings → Environment Variables, then redeploy.
# Diagnose (no secret exposed): open GET /api/analyze in the browser — groqApiKeyPresent should be true.
GROQ_API_KEY=
# Optional fallback if the key was saved under another name:
# GROQ_KEY=

# Model for image analysis. Must be a Groq vision / multimodal model.
# Default: meta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct (see Groq vision docs).
# Text-only models cannot analyze photos.
# GROQ_MODEL=meta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct

# Text model for /api/analyze-measurements (no vision). Default: llama-3.3-70b-versatile
# GROQ_MEASUREMENTS_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile
